# we do exactly same computations in both top-down dp(recursively) or in a
# bottom-up dp(tabluation/iterative).

# in fact bottom-up approach is just a topological sorted computational order
# in the subproblem dependency directed acyclic graph.

                     --------->---------
                     |                 |
        fn-3 -----> fn-2------>fn-1 ---->fn
         |                    |
         ----------->----------

# we can save storage space in bottom-up approach
# we need constant space but linear time in linear DP.

